+ use get() and set(), do not modify attributes without set() !




// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// bind() and bindAll
//
// in JavaScript, when you pass a function as a callback, its value for "this" 
// is lost. Using these functions allows to determine the value of "this"
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// Binds a number of methods on the object, specified by methodNames, to be run 
// in the context of that object whenever they are invoked.
_.bindAll(object, [*methodNames])

// Bind a function to an object, meaning that whenever the function is called, 
// the value of this will be the object.
_.bind(function, object, [*arguments])





